 # Apex KB
 
+## Capability-first execution router
+
+Choose one path before reading the rest of this skill.
+
+### Connector-only semantic compiler
+
+Use this path when you can read and write repository files but cannot run terminal Python.
+
+```yaml
+connector_only:
+  role: whole_artifact_semantic_author
+  may_read:
+    - operator-selected source files or source slices
+    - references/kb-contract.md
+    - templates/ingest-analysis-template.md
+    - templates/wiki-page-templates.md
+  may_create_or_fully_rewrite:
+    - ingest-analysis/*.md
+    - wiki/summaries/*.md
+    - wiki/concepts/*.md
+    - wiki/entities/*.md
+    - log/connector-compile-*.json
+  must_not:
+    - partially edit an existing file
+    - append to or hand-maintain wiki/index.md
+    - update source manifests, hashes, ledgers, or audit registries
+    - touch manifests/phase0/, derived/search/, or outputs/queries/
+    - claim deterministic validation
+  maximum_state: compiled_unvalidated
+```
+
+Compile one page per context window. For each page:
+
+1. Read only the source slice, the canonical page contract, and the relevant page template.
+2. Author one complete new page or one complete whole-file rewrite.
+3. Re-read that page and fail the self-check if any item below is true.
+4. Write the page only after the self-check passes.
+5. Record the page and self-check result in one whole-file connector compile manifest.
+6. Move to the next page only after the current page is complete. Do not batch multiple pages into one drafting pass.
+
+Connector authoring self-check:
+
+- no placeholder or template text remains;
+- `source_refs` is present and usable;
+- all Phase 2 value-contract sections are present;
+- summary pages contain at least two specific key claims unless the page is explicitly a valid narrow exception;
+- concept pages do not collapse to one thin claim;
+- Macro, Meso, and Micro each contain substantive, non-placeholder content;
+- concept Micro content contains concrete evidence rather than generic restatement;
+- every key claim has a source pointer;
+- at least one real query route is present;
+- broad summary pages use more than one source when the deterministic profile requires source breadth.
+
+These checks mirror the current terminal quality reason codes, but they do not certify the page. `apex_kb.py quality --strict` remains authoritative. If the terminal result disagrees, the terminal result controls and the checklist must be reconciled in the same repair.
+
+The connector compile manifest is a single JSON file under `log/` containing:
+
+```yaml
+required_fields:
+  run_id: string
+  executor_surface: connector_only
+  deterministic_steps_executed: []
+  state: compiled_unvalidated
+  pages:
+    - path: repo_relative_path
+      operation: create | full_rewrite
+      self_check: pass | fail
+      failed_checks: []
+  terminal_handoff_required: true
+  required_terminal_actions:
+    - rebuild wiki index
+    - rebuild retrieval index
+    - run lint --strict
+    - run quality --strict
+    - run status and stale checks
+```
+
+If no terminal executor is available, stop at `compiled_unvalidated`. The KB is not `query_ready`, regardless of connector read-back or self-check results.
+
+### Terminal-capable executor
+
+Use the operating contract and procedure below. Terminal validation is required for any state above `compiled_unvalidated`.
